The paper deals with the task of sketch based image retrieval (SBIR) using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various strategies for weight sharing, pre-processing, data augmentation, and dimensionality reduction, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML) research. Hence, cs.LG is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for measuring similarity between sketches and photographs. Therefore, cs.IR is the third most likely sub-category. The paper evaluates its proposed models on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research. Hence, cs.MM is the fourth most likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes and evaluates several CNN architectures, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.AI is the fifth most likely sub-category.
